def get_gender_POW(message):
    replies = []

    if "male" in message:
        replies.append("What about your approach to women?")
    elif "female" in message:
        replies.append("What about your approach to men?")
    elif "gender" in message:
        replies.append("What about your role in society?")
    else:
        replies.append("What about your personal gender identity?")

    res = random.choice(replies)
    return res, "string"

def process_gender_POW(message):
    if "gender" in message:
        res = "I suck. If you have a roughly 50% chance of getting **** right, you gotta lose, and I lost."
        return res

    if "approach" in message:
        res = "Well, the straight up answer is zero, buy the way. The problem is Mr Shit,.Stop being such a beta male."
        return res

    if "role" in message:
        res = "Are you Bieber? Or my little pony"
        return res

    if "identity" in message:
        res = ["I know, I'm gay", "Mojito is good balding hair out there in town", "I'm paid for this talk"]
        res = random.choice(res)
        return res

    return "I don't know what to say", "string"

I believe in equality! In the future, everyone will have equal rights and everyone will be treated with equal respect! I don’t believe in being a man or a woman any longer. We are simply humans! Nothing else. I am very much for gender equality and everyone to be treated equally although not all of my friends agree with me on this issue. What is sad is that we do not treat others as well as we treat others. It is sad that we as women already have stereotypes placed on us and yet we are told that we can be anything and do anything (as I love the saying). When I grew up, I wanted to be a marine biologist and it was because of this that I got pursuit of a biomedical science degree. It saddens me to know that nowadays, I, especially if I dream of doing anything related to animals. People will tell me that I cannot be because that is what a man does. It makes me wonder where the humanity is, in so many cases where women or men are not treated equally. It really does make me sad to know that women cannot cultivate their dreams because of the background that they come from or because they were brought up to believe that that is the only path they can fashion their lives. That should not be the case nowadays.
Everyone should stay true to their desires whether it is a man or a woman. It pains me to see them feeling ashamed about what they want to become because they feel as if they are letting people down. I believe in everyone’s dreams. It really does surprise me when people say, “ How can you do that? It is already so competitive! Who do you expect to open a business and be successful?” Well, I believe that if you work hard, you will make it.
Once again, that is how I feel about families; that is different. There are the family values that some of us are taught. I am a firm believer in family and families have been around for ages and will continue to be around. Families have helped us grow, nothing more than that. No matter how old we are, it is always great to have our families by our sides. It saddens me to see families divided. How can some people be mean to their family members? They deserve better! dotenv(bin("./config.env"));
